Adjust rack to top position, then preheat oven to 450 degrees. Lightly oil a #baking sheet{}. Wash and dry all produce. Slice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Toss on prepared sheet with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{3%teaspoon}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Bake until lightly browned and tender, about ~{20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, mince or grate @Garlic{4%clove}(minced or grated). Peel @Blood Orange{2}, then slice crosswise into rounds. Thinly slice @Chives{½%ounce}.

Pat @Sirloin Steak{28%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat. Remove from pan and set aside to rest for ~{5%minutes}. Wipe out pan.

Once potatoes have roasted 20 minutes, flip and evenly sprinkle with @Parmesan Cheese{½%cup}. Return to oven until cheese is browned and melted, ~{5-10%minutes}.

Heat @Butter{3%tablespoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Reduce heat to low, then stir in chives until thoroughly combined. Turn off heat. Season generously with salt and pepper.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine orange rounds, @Mixed Greens{4%ounce}, a drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper. Slice steak against the grain. Divide salad, finished potatoes, and steak between plates. Top steak with sauce.